# Environment variable contract — ${PROJECT_NAME}
#
# Copy to `.env` (git-ignored) and fill in real values. Never commit `.env` or paste
# real values into prompts, logs, or tool arguments (see .agent/SAFETY.md).
# List every env var the project reads here, with a placeholder value, so the
# contract is documented without leaking secrets. Add new keys to
# docs/CANONICAL_SOURCES.md when they become part of a public contract.

# --- Example entries (replace with your project's real keys) ---
# API_BASE_URL=<service base URL>
# API_KEY=<your API key>
# DATABASE_URL=<connection string without embedded credentials where possible>
# LOG_LEVEL=info
